  <div id="bodyleft">
    <h2><font color="#0c4f62">Competitions</font></h2>
    <h3>Win the Chance to design your very own Milano Leotard!</h3>
<p><a href="http://www.milano-pro-sport.com" target="_blank"><img src="images/Evolution banner.GIF" alt="Milano banner" width="640" height="150" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>To celebrate the launch of  'Making the Grade' by Cate Shearwater,  Egmont Publishing have teamed up with  top leotard designers <a href="http://www.milano-pro-sport.com">Milano Pro Sport</a> to<br />
  bring you the Somersaults and Dreams:<br />
</p>
<h3>Design a Leotard Competition</h3>
<p>It's very simple. Just fill in the blank template by clicking on the template image below which will downoad on to your computer as a PDF document, save it locally and it can then be printed out. </p>
<p><a href="images/E2309_DesignLeotardCompetition_SaD_V4.pdf"><img src="images/leotard-template.jpg" alt="leotard template" width="640" height="447" border="0" /></a></p>
<p> Then use  pens, pencils, paints, glitter, glue, sequins to design your dream leotard.<br />
  </p>
<h3>Design ideas<br />
</h3>
<p>Your leotard can be long or short-sleeved, and in any style you choose! If you're looking for some top design inspiration, why not check out the Milano website <a href="http://www.milano-pro-sport.com">www.milano-pro-sport.com.</a> After all the competition is judged by the Milano design team and the new Spring 2015 collection Evolution is already causing mass excitement amongst all leotard enthusiasts! The current 'Raise Your Game' collection (which has over fifty leotards) is also available now, so you are sure to find some spark for your ideas somewhere! <br />
</p>
<h3>Top Tips<br />
</h3>
<p>'The main thing we try to look for when designing is what is in fashion at the time,' says Milano Head Designer, Louise. 'Try to look at the designs in your favourite shops or, in Vogue, at London Fashion Week and on fashion blogs- there's so many out there! Pay attention to the colour combinations and shapes; and then let that inspire your leotard design.'</p>
<p>Entries will be judged by Milano's design team and<br />
</p>
<p><strong>THE WINNING ENTRY WILL BE MADE INTO A REAL LEOTARD!</strong><br />
</p>
<p>Five runners up will each receive a £40 Milano gift voucher and a copy of<br />
  Cate Shearwater's book, Making the Grade. All short-listed designs will also<br />
  be featured on the Cate Shearwater website.<br />
  </p>
<p><strong>To enter</strong>, send your design in a stamped addressed envelope to:<br />
  <br />
  SOMERSAULTS AND DREAMS COMPETITION, <br />
  EGMONT PUBLISHING,<br />
  THE YELLOW BUILDING, <br />
  1 NICHOLAS ROAD, <br />
  LONDON, <br />
  W11 4AN</p>
<p><strong>or</strong> you can send your entries via email to: <a href="mailto:pressoffice@euk.egmont.com">pressoffice@euk.egmont.com</a><br />
</p>
<p><strong>Competition closes Friday 7th August 2015</strong></p>
<p><strong>Rules for entry:
</strong><br /><ul>
  <li>Only one entry per person</li><br />
  <li>The winning design will be picked by a team including Milano Designers</li><br />
  <li>The winner will be announced on 11th September on the  Cate Shearwater and Milano websites.</li><br />
  <li>The winner should be prepared to take part in Cate Shearwater and Milano publicity around the competition</li><br />
  <li>All designs must be original. No liability is accepted by Cate Shearwater or Milano for any copying of which we are unaware</li><br />
  <li>Postal entries will not be returned to sender<br />
    <br />
  </li></ul>
  For further terms and conditions please visit: 
  <br />
  <a href="http://www.egmont.co.uk/competitionterms/" target="_blank">http://www.egmont.co.uk/competitionterms/</a><br />
  <br />
